## 3. The Data Ingestion Flow (ETL)

To demonstrate how the data gets populated:
1. **Source Data**: Synthetic patient records are located in [my-ehr-guide/Data/fhir](file:///c:/hekma/Hekma/my-ehr-guide/Data/fhir). These are generated using **Synthea**, a realistic patient generator.
2. **Ingestion Pipeline**: The [backend/etl.py](file:///c:/hekma/Hekma/backend/etl.py) script reads the JSON files, extracts patient metadata, structures the records (observations, conditions, encounters, medications, immunizations, allergies), creates indexes, and merges them into Neo4j nodes.

